cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper deals with unsupervised learning of visual structure using deep neural networks, specifically in the context of predicting future frames in synthetic video sequences. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial loss and the development of internal models, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep neural networks also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the representation of three-dimensional objects, which could potentially place it in the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics).
